hands_on_practices.problem:
A discrete random variable $X$ can take one of three values from the set $S = \{10, 20, 30\}$. Each value is equally likely to occur. The probability mass function (PMF) is given by:
$$
P(X=x) = \begin{cases}
\frac{1}{3}  \text{if } x \in \{10, 20, 30\} \\
0  \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
$$
Derive the variance of the random variable $X$, denoted as $\mathrm{Var}(X)$.
